text.tspan: Who Americans spend their time with, by age
Average time spent with others is measured in minutes per day, and shown by the age of the respondent. This is based on averages from
Data source: American Time Use Survey (2009-2019) and Lindberg (2017)
Note: Relationships used to categorize people are not exhaustive. Additionally, time spent with multiple people can be counted more than once (e.g. attending a party
with friends and partner counts for both “friends” and “partner”).
